WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:03.752
NARRATOR:
Previously on Vampire Diaries:

00:03.920 --> 00:07.506
Vampires and werewolves used to roam free
until a shaman put a curse on them.

00:07.674 --> 00:11.593
Werewolves can only turn on a full moon
and vampires are weakened by the sun.

00:11.761 --> 00:14.471
The werewolf part of the curse,
it's sealed with moonstone.

00:14.639 --> 00:16.347
He told me about your ex, Katherine.

00:16.516 --> 00:19.018
- You must be Elena.
- How do we look exactly alike?

00:19.185 --> 00:21.854
No. Damon, don't. You need me.
Elena's in danger.

00:22.022 --> 00:25.107
- Moonstone is what breaks the curse.
- Sacrifice breaks it.

00:25.275 --> 00:27.276
The blood of the doppelgänger. You.

00:27.444 --> 00:30.237
I wanna be with you, Stefan,
but I need to wake up...

00:30.405 --> 00:32.656
...and know that the people I love
are safe.

00:32.824 --> 00:35.576
- You were running from something.
- Everyone has a past.

00:35.744 --> 00:37.244
The Originals,
Rose and I pissed them off.

00:37.412 --> 00:39.663
- What did you do?
- He trusted Katerina Petrova.

00:39.831 --> 00:41.457
Elijah, I beg your forgiveness.

00:43.000 --> 00:49.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:50.967 --> 00:52.384
[WOMAN YELLING]

00:52.677 --> 00:54.636
[IN BULGARIAN]

01:00.477 --> 01:01.977
[BABY WAILING]

01:39.891 --> 01:41.350
[BOTH SOBBING]

01:46.856 --> 01:48.774
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

01:54.531 --> 01:55.948
Hello, Elena.

01:56.116 --> 01:57.491
Stefan here?

01:57.659 --> 01:59.701
He called. Said it was important.

02:00.870 --> 02:02.621
Right this way.

02:06.501 --> 02:08.210
Hey.

02:09.378 --> 02:10.586
What is this about?

02:14.926 --> 02:16.635
You.

02:24.769 --> 02:27.688
Okay, I only know what I've picked up
over the years.

02:27.897 --> 02:30.190
And I don't know what's true
and what's not true.

02:30.400 --> 02:33.986
That's the problem with all of this
vampire crap. But Klaus I know is real.

02:34.154 --> 02:37.114
- Who is he?
- He's one of the Originals. He's a legend.

02:37.282 --> 02:39.616
- First generation of vampires.
- Like Elijah.

02:39.784 --> 02:42.828
No, Elijah was the Easter bunny
compared to Klaus.

02:42.996 --> 02:45.247
He's a foot soldier.
Klaus is the real deal.

02:45.415 --> 02:47.916
Klaus is known to be the oldest.

02:48.084 --> 02:49.960
Okay, so you're saying...

02:50.128 --> 02:53.505
...that the oldest vampire in the history
of time is coming after me?

02:53.673 --> 02:54.715
- Yes.
- No.

02:54.924 --> 02:56.842
I mean, if what she's saying is true...

02:57.010 --> 02:58.051
ROSE:
Which it is.

02:58.219 --> 03:00.429
- You're not saying this so we don't kill you?
- I'm not.

03:00.597 --> 03:02.639
Then we're looking at a solid maybe.

03:04.434 --> 03:07.769
Look, Elijah's dead, right?
No one else even knows that you exist.

03:07.937 --> 03:09.813
- Not that you know of.
- Not helping.

03:09.981 --> 03:12.524
I've never even met anyone
who's laid eyes on him.

03:12.692 --> 03:16.069
I mean, we're talking centuries of truth
mixed with fiction.

03:16.237 --> 03:19.531
We don't know what's real.
He could be some stupid bedtime story.

03:19.699 --> 03:21.575
He's real. And he doesn't give up.

03:21.743 --> 03:25.579
If he wants something, he gets it.
If you're not afraid then you're an idiot.

03:25.747 --> 03:28.582
All right, we're shaking.
You made your point.

03:31.502 --> 03:32.961
Where are you going?

03:33.630 --> 03:36.506
School. I'm late.

03:36.674 --> 03:38.634
I'll grab my stuff. I'll go with you.

03:38.801 --> 03:40.052
That's okay.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.262
I know where it is.

03:45.725 --> 03:46.808
DAMON:
She's in denial.

03:49.562 --> 03:51.230
Shut up, Damon.

03:52.982 --> 03:54.483
[JEREMY LAUGHS]

03:54.692 --> 03:56.485
Here, I got it.

03:57.487 --> 03:59.863
- Thanks.
- Yeah. Uh...

04:00.031 --> 04:04.117
- Where's Elena?
- She's, um, actually running late today.

04:04.285 --> 04:07.162
You wanna hang out at the Grill,
shoot some pool?

04:07.330 --> 04:09.039
Winner runs the table.

04:09.207 --> 04:11.458
- Uh, why?
- Why what?

04:11.626 --> 04:14.836
Well, you never asked me to play a game
of pool before. So why now?

04:15.004 --> 04:19.298
Uh, I don't know.
I thought that would be fun. Never mind.

04:19.509 --> 04:20.591
No, hey. Okay.

04:21.636 --> 04:24.137
- Sure. It's just...
- Just what?

04:25.890 --> 04:28.725
It's just you're Elena's brother and...

04:32.814 --> 04:37.276
- Sure. It's just I'm really bad at pool.
- Yeah, yeah. I thought you might be.

04:37.443 --> 04:40.404
Hey, excuse me. Do you guys know
which way's the office?

04:41.197 --> 04:43.031
Yeah. Yeah.
Through the double doors...

04:43.199 --> 04:45.867
...straight ahead, quick left
and then your first right.

04:46.035 --> 04:48.745
- You must be new here.
- Yeah, I am. It's hard to hide it.

04:48.913 --> 04:51.373
- My name's Luka.
- I'm Jeremy. This is Bonnie.

04:51.749 --> 04:53.333
Hi, Bonnie.

04:55.461 --> 04:58.714
Anyway, I'm headed in that direction.
Why don't you follow me?

04:58.881 --> 05:01.216
- It can get confusing.
- Okay. Thanks, man.

05:01.384 --> 05:03.593
It's nice to meet you, Bonnie.

05:05.972 --> 05:09.433
Tell everyone I wasn't feeling well
and I went home from school.

05:09.600 --> 05:11.601
I can't believe I'm agreeing to this.

05:11.769 --> 05:12.811
I'm a terrible liar.

05:12.979 --> 05:15.272
Keep Stefan busy.
I don't want him knowing what I'm up to.

05:15.440 --> 05:16.898
I'm even worse at duplicity.

05:17.066 --> 05:18.191
And you know this.

05:18.359 --> 05:20.193
ELENA:
You managed to keep me occupied...

05:20.361 --> 05:22.154
...when Katherine paid Stefan a visit.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.239
Yeah, because she threatened me.

05:24.407 --> 05:27.701
Not that I'm saying that you should use
that as a tactic. It's...

05:27.869 --> 05:29.369
Stefan's gonna see through me.

05:29.579 --> 05:33.081
Caroline, as my friend,
do you promise or not?

05:33.249 --> 05:34.416
[SIGHS]

05:35.460 --> 05:38.462
You had to break out
the girlfriend code.

05:38.629 --> 05:40.422
Okay.

05:40.590 --> 05:42.716
- I promise.
- Okay.

05:45.636 --> 05:47.304
Why don't you want Stefan to know?

05:47.472 --> 05:50.307
Because he would never be okay
with me doing this.

05:51.100 --> 05:52.434
[SIGHS]

05:57.523 --> 05:59.399
Are you sure you wanna do this?

05:59.609 --> 06:02.652
Yes. She's the only one who knows
the truth about Klaus...

06:02.820 --> 06:04.488
...who can tell me how to stop him.

06:04.655 --> 06:08.742
But you're asking for the truth from
someone who's probably never given it.

06:09.243 --> 06:13.288
- Are you sure about this?
- Yes, I can't just sit back and wait.

06:13.456 --> 06:14.790
I have to know, Caroline.

06:19.295 --> 06:20.712
Please.

06:51.869 --> 06:53.662
ELENA:
Katherine?

06:58.543 --> 06:59.668
I'll be okay from here.

07:01.045 --> 07:02.712
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

07:22.608 --> 07:24.526
Hello, Elena.

07:29.991 --> 07:32.242
You come to watch me wither away?

07:33.995 --> 07:35.704
Goodbye, Caroline.

07:36.497 --> 07:40.292
As long as I stay on this side
of the door, she can't hurt me.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.210
Please.

07:49.010 --> 07:50.218
Stefan know you're here?

07:50.845 --> 07:52.387
I brought you some things.

07:52.555 --> 07:55.140
You came to bribe me.
What is it that you want?

07:56.476 --> 07:58.894
I want you to tell me about Klaus.

07:59.228 --> 08:02.022
Hmm. You've been busy.

08:05.776 --> 08:07.068
I also brought you this.

08:09.030 --> 08:10.822
It's your family history.

08:10.990 --> 08:13.783
It says in here that the family line
ended with you.

08:16.287 --> 08:17.829
Obviously, that's not true.

08:17.997 --> 08:22.209
You think that if you brought me
some family keepsake I'd open up?

08:25.171 --> 08:27.297
I also brought you this.

08:28.633 --> 08:30.467
[GASPING]

08:31.552 --> 08:32.719
You don't look so good.

08:32.886 --> 08:34.763
How long before
your body shuts down?

08:34.931 --> 08:36.097
Ten, 20 years?

08:36.307 --> 08:38.558
Must be painful to desiccate
and mummify.

08:39.018 --> 08:40.936
I can't even imagine.

08:55.576 --> 08:57.744
[KATHERINE GASPING]

09:14.095 --> 09:16.429
You have the Petrova fire.

09:23.396 --> 09:25.146
More blood?

09:32.905 --> 09:35.615
It's a long story, Klaus and I.

09:36.492 --> 09:41.621
Goes all the way back to England, 1492,
after I left Bulgaria.

09:41.789 --> 09:45.000
Or was thrown out.

09:46.335 --> 09:47.627
Thrown out?

09:47.795 --> 09:51.881
My family, your true ancestors...

09:52.675 --> 09:57.012
...they disowned me. My indiscretions
were not tolerated at that time.

09:57.179 --> 09:58.847
I had a baby out of wedlock.

09:59.015 --> 10:00.181
The shame.

10:00.975 --> 10:02.017
It was kept secret.

10:02.310 --> 10:03.351
Mm-hm.

10:03.519 --> 10:05.020
My baby was given away.

10:06.022 --> 10:09.107
I was banished to England
and I had to learn to adjust.

10:09.275 --> 10:11.610
So I quickly became English.

10:11.777 --> 10:14.696
It was there that I caught the eye
of a nobleman named Klaus.

10:15.156 --> 10:19.159
I was taken with him at first,
till I found out what he was...

10:19.327 --> 10:21.536
...and what he wanted from me.

10:21.704 --> 10:23.413
And then I ran like hell.

10:29.045 --> 10:30.503
Ah!

10:32.632 --> 10:33.923
[VAMPIRE GROWLING]

10:34.800 --> 10:36.343
ELIJAH:
She's here.

10:37.219 --> 10:38.345
[SHOUTS]
Katerina?

10:38.971 --> 10:40.847
I know you're near.

10:41.015 --> 10:43.475
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
I can smell your blood.

10:44.852 --> 10:46.728
It's pointless to run.

10:46.937 --> 10:48.730
Klaus will find you wherever you are.

10:50.024 --> 10:52.734
This way.
There's more blood over there.

10:57.823 --> 10:59.699
[WHIMPERING]

11:14.006 --> 11:16.591
Head east.
I can't lead them astray much longer.

11:16.759 --> 11:18.551
- I can't run anymore.
- Never mind.

11:18.719 --> 11:21.096
There's a cottage. You'll be safe there.

11:22.264 --> 11:23.890
Go now. Go.

11:24.350 --> 11:25.475
ELENA:
So...

11:28.187 --> 11:29.562
...what did Klaus want?

11:29.730 --> 11:32.524
Same thing that he'll want from you.

11:32.692 --> 11:34.109
He wants to break the curse.

11:34.276 --> 11:36.236
By sacrificing
the Petrova doppelgänger.

11:36.779 --> 11:40.782
He wanted to drain every single drop
of blood from my body.

11:43.494 --> 11:45.120
[SNIFFLING]

11:45.538 --> 11:47.372
DAMON:
All right, Rosebud...

11:48.791 --> 11:50.583
...I need some answers.

11:51.419 --> 11:54.462
Don't tell me you're crying
because Trevor lost his head.

11:54.630 --> 11:56.256
You always been this sensitive?

11:56.424 --> 11:59.134
A little vampire switch.
You can "pfft" for this very reason.

11:59.301 --> 12:02.554
- Takes the emotion out of it.
- You switch yours, I'll switch mine.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.305
- Is that a dig?
- An observation.

12:04.473 --> 12:06.975
Being in love with your brother's
girlfriend must be difficult.

12:07.143 --> 12:10.478
- I'm not in love with anyone.
- You wanna try that again?

12:14.024 --> 12:15.483
Don't get on my bad side.

12:15.651 --> 12:17.277
Then show me your good side.

12:18.738 --> 12:21.489
- How do I find Klaus?
- You don't find Klaus, he finds you.

12:21.657 --> 12:25.160
Somebody's gonna know somebody
who knows where he is, right?

12:25.327 --> 12:28.663
Add another 200 somebodies to that
and you're still not even close.

12:28.831 --> 12:31.833
Humor me. You got in touch with Elijah.
How'd you do it?

12:32.001 --> 12:34.919
Through a very low somebody
on the totem pole.

12:35.087 --> 12:36.838
A guy named Slater in Richmond.

12:37.256 --> 12:38.506
Perfect. I'll drive.

12:38.674 --> 12:40.759
No. You forget not all of us
can do sun.

12:42.428 --> 12:43.636
Then you drive.

12:45.055 --> 12:46.639
Come on.

12:48.517 --> 12:50.477
- Stefan. Hey.
- Hey.

12:50.644 --> 12:52.979
Um, I need to talk to you.
Where are you going?

12:53.147 --> 12:55.523
Uh, Elena went home sick.
I wanna go check up on her.

12:55.691 --> 12:58.067
- Ditcher.
- Yeah, I'm kind of worried about her.

12:58.694 --> 13:01.529
You know what, of course you are.
Go ahead.

13:01.697 --> 13:03.490
You know what, we can talk later.

13:05.868 --> 13:08.328
Uh, talk about what?

13:10.289 --> 13:12.874
I might have done something.

13:14.794 --> 13:15.877
What did you do?

13:17.296 --> 13:19.714
Told Tyler I'm a vampire.

13:26.555 --> 13:29.891
What does the Petrova bloodline
have to do with Klaus?

13:35.481 --> 13:37.899
It's really tedious...

13:41.737 --> 13:45.198
...but the curse was bound
by the sacrifice of Petrova blood.

13:45.658 --> 13:48.576
Witches are crafty with their spells.

13:49.411 --> 13:53.248
The doppelgänger was created
as a way to be able to undo the spell.

13:53.707 --> 13:57.335
Once the doppelgänger reappeared,
the curse can be broken.

13:58.504 --> 14:00.755
So you ran before he killed you.

14:01.924 --> 14:03.758
Something like that.

14:14.061 --> 14:17.105
Help. Please help me.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.568
Please. Help me.

14:21.735 --> 14:24.612
- I don't invite strangers into my home.
- No...

14:25.447 --> 14:26.531
...Trevor.

14:26.699 --> 14:28.116
He said that you'd help me.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.450
ROSE:
Damn him.

14:29.618 --> 14:32.203
Always making promises
I don't wanna keep.

14:34.206 --> 14:35.290
Let the girl in.

14:42.089 --> 14:43.923
Bring her water and something to eat.

14:47.928 --> 14:49.804
You must be Rose. Thank you.

14:51.265 --> 14:52.974
Trevor said to show you this.

14:53.183 --> 14:56.227
To prove I am who I say.
That you would help me to freedom.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.396
You stole this from Klaus?

14:58.564 --> 15:02.442
It was to be part of the sacrifice ritual
so I grabbed it and made my escape.

15:02.610 --> 15:06.154
People do not escape from Klaus.
Everyone who tries ends up in his grasp.

15:06.322 --> 15:07.947
Anyone who helps them dies.

15:08.115 --> 15:10.950
- I know the risk you bring on yourself.
- I risk nothing.

15:11.118 --> 15:14.829
I will bring you back to Klaus
and beg him to show us both mercy.

15:14.997 --> 15:16.789
KATHERINE:
No!

15:32.765 --> 15:35.099
Back entrance. How convenient.

15:35.267 --> 15:38.478
That's the point.
We can't all have little daylight rings.

15:38.646 --> 15:42.106
- How do you know this guy's even here?
- I called him. He's always here.

15:42.274 --> 15:45.944
Good. Just one thing.
If you're setting me up in any way...

15:46.111 --> 15:49.197
...I will rip your heart out
and shove it down your throat.

15:49.365 --> 15:50.865
Something I'm very good at.

15:53.369 --> 15:55.787
I'm older than you and stronger.

15:55.955 --> 15:57.997
Don't get on my bad side.

16:00.334 --> 16:01.876
You can trust me.

16:08.217 --> 16:10.259
[SOFT ROCK MUSIC PLAYS]

16:15.474 --> 16:19.519
- Whoa, what about the sunlight?
- Doubled paned and tempered.

16:19.687 --> 16:22.522
UV rays can't penetrate.
You see the appeal now?

16:22.690 --> 16:24.399
That and the free Wi-Fi.

16:24.566 --> 16:25.858
- Oh, hey.
- Hey.

16:26.026 --> 16:27.360
- How are you?
- Good.

16:27.861 --> 16:29.737
I saw you come.
What are you doing here?

16:30.197 --> 16:32.907
That's a long story.
But I want you to meet...

16:34.326 --> 16:35.410
Damon Salvatore.

16:35.911 --> 16:37.870
Turned 1864, Mystic Falls...

16:38.038 --> 16:40.873
...by Katherine Pierce,
a.k.a. Katerina Petrova.

16:43.585 --> 16:45.253
So I take it I was right?

16:45.421 --> 16:47.839
What I told you about the tomb
under the church?

16:48.007 --> 16:51.509
- Yes, it was right. Thank you for the tip.
- Yeah.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.428
It's nice to meet you.

16:56.432 --> 16:58.099
Maybe.

16:58.600 --> 17:00.268
What's going on, Rose?

17:00.436 --> 17:01.853
Where's, uh, Trevor?

17:10.279 --> 17:13.531
Rose never ended up taking you
back to Klaus, did she?

17:13.699 --> 17:14.824
No.

17:15.284 --> 17:17.910
But not because
she had a change of heart.

17:21.290 --> 17:22.373
It's nightfall.

17:22.958 --> 17:24.791
Time to go.

17:25.711 --> 17:27.170
[KATHERINE GASPS]

17:27.378 --> 17:30.882
- When did this happen?
- In the woods. I tripped.

17:31.050 --> 17:33.301
That's a lie. I would have smelled it.

17:34.428 --> 17:37.764
I'd rather die than go back to Klaus.
Please just let me die.

17:37.931 --> 17:39.974
If you die, then Trevor dies with you.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.268
No. No...!

17:46.690 --> 17:48.483
[GASPING]

17:51.945 --> 17:53.237
Where is she?

17:54.490 --> 17:56.491
You have set us both
on a path of death.

17:56.658 --> 17:59.494
I hope Klaus sees the honor
in returning that girl to him.

17:59.661 --> 18:01.120
TREVOR:
He will sacrifice her.

18:01.288 --> 18:02.497
Then so be it.

18:03.957 --> 18:05.166
I love her, Rose.

18:07.795 --> 18:08.878
He'll kill you.

18:11.256 --> 18:13.674
He will not stop
until he has all of our heads.

18:16.470 --> 18:18.513
Then we shall run until we die.

18:19.181 --> 18:20.515
[CLATTERING]

18:38.117 --> 18:40.701
You killed yourself?

18:41.036 --> 18:43.246
Klaus needed a human doppelgänger.

18:43.413 --> 18:46.207
As a vampire,
I was no longer any use to him.

18:46.792 --> 18:50.878
But it didn't work. You didn't escape.
You've been running ever since.

18:51.046 --> 18:53.464
I underestimated
his spirit for vengeance.

18:53.632 --> 18:55.967
Living out of a suitcase
is better than dying...

18:56.135 --> 18:59.387
...so that you could have your blood
spilled over some silly rock.

19:00.889 --> 19:02.223
What's wrong?

19:03.058 --> 19:04.559
Afraid I'm right?

19:04.726 --> 19:06.727
You don't wanna die?

19:06.895 --> 19:08.896
There's another way out.

19:13.318 --> 19:20.324
Better hurry. Your opportunity
is going, going, going, and gone.

19:25.539 --> 19:27.081
I made the other choice.

19:27.249 --> 19:28.541
[KATHERINE GASPS]

19:30.586 --> 19:33.129
TREVOR:
What did you do, Katerina?

19:34.756 --> 19:36.132
I would have helped you live.

19:36.300 --> 19:38.467
You would have helped me run.

19:38.635 --> 19:41.137
That was never going to be enough.

19:46.685 --> 19:47.852
It was enough for me.

19:50.606 --> 19:52.273
Oh, do you not see, Trevor?

19:52.774 --> 19:55.276
She used you to help her escape
and me to turn her.

19:55.819 --> 19:57.361
Klaus will see our role in this.

19:57.571 --> 19:58.863
And for that, I'm sorry.

19:59.865 --> 20:00.948
As am I...

20:02.201 --> 20:03.826
...for this.
- No!

20:04.453 --> 20:05.494
Oh!

20:07.915 --> 20:09.457
[GASPING]

20:09.708 --> 20:10.791
Please understand.

20:10.959 --> 20:13.794
You have just signed
our death sentence.

20:15.130 --> 20:16.964
Better you die than I.

20:19.635 --> 20:24.138
Rose and Trevor spent the last 500 years
running because you used them.

20:24.306 --> 20:25.473
Trevor just got killed.

20:25.641 --> 20:28.309
Never thought
he would've lasted that long.

20:28.477 --> 20:31.187
You don't even care
that you ruined their lives.

20:31.355 --> 20:33.314
I was looking out for myself, Elena.

20:33.857 --> 20:36.317
I will always look out for myself.

20:36.485 --> 20:39.111
If you're smart, you'll do the same.

20:54.044 --> 20:58.339
Sorry to drag you here, but if I don't eat,
I get those kill-innocent-people urges.

20:58.840 --> 21:00.508
Tyler has those, too, by the way.

21:00.676 --> 21:03.552
- Yeah, what else did you say to him?
CAROLINE: Not much.

21:03.720 --> 21:06.764
I was trying to keep the questions
to a minimum.

21:09.393 --> 21:11.185
- Are you mad?
STEFAN: Yes, Caroline.

21:11.353 --> 21:12.937
As a matter of fact, I am mad.

21:13.146 --> 21:15.356
You put yourself at risk.
If Damon finds out...

21:15.524 --> 21:19.944
- But you're not gonna tell him.
- No, of course not. He would kill you.

21:20.279 --> 21:21.779
Always looking out for me.

21:21.947 --> 21:25.032
Yeah, well, you don't exactly
make it very easy on me.

21:25.200 --> 21:28.703
Then why do you do it?
Why are you such a good friend to me?

21:29.204 --> 21:32.581
I don't know.
I guess you, uh, remind me of someone.

21:33.667 --> 21:35.876
My best friend, Lexi.

21:38.046 --> 21:40.047
- You have a friend?
- Heh, heh.

21:40.215 --> 21:44.051
You say that with such a discouraging
amount of surprise, Caroline.

21:44.219 --> 21:47.305
No, I just... Sorry, I just...

21:47.973 --> 21:50.057
Tell me about her.

21:51.727 --> 21:53.894
I will, some other time. I gotta go.

21:54.062 --> 21:56.564
Wait, no. What do I do about Tyler?

21:56.732 --> 22:02.903
I don't want Damon to kill him because
there is a full moon coming up...

22:03.322 --> 22:05.823
...and Tyler's totally freaking out
about it.

22:10.245 --> 22:11.787
Hey, Bonnie.

22:11.955 --> 22:13.914
Hey. Luka.

22:14.082 --> 22:15.916
- How was your first day?
- It was great.

22:16.710 --> 22:19.003
I would like you to introduce you
to my dad.

22:19.212 --> 22:21.088
Hi, I'm Bonnie Bennett.

22:21.256 --> 22:23.424
Dr. Martin. Jonas Martin.

22:23.592 --> 22:25.676
It's nice to meet you, Bonnie Bennett.

22:25.844 --> 22:29.472
- Would you like to join us?
- Oh, I'm meeting a friend.

22:29.639 --> 22:33.267
But he's not here yet, so sure.

22:34.102 --> 22:36.312
Oh, yes. Please have a seat.

22:37.939 --> 22:42.109
- So, um, where'd you move from?
- Louisiana.

22:42.611 --> 22:44.820
- That's a big change.
- I'll say.

22:46.615 --> 22:47.865
It's not so bad here.

22:48.784 --> 22:49.867
It's looking up.

22:50.285 --> 22:51.702
Bennett, huh?

22:51.870 --> 22:55.623
I knew some Bennetts when I did
my residency in Massachusetts.

22:56.124 --> 22:58.542
Do you have any family from Salem?

23:00.253 --> 23:01.379
Actually, I do.

23:03.131 --> 23:05.049
What do you know?
Small world, right?

23:05.217 --> 23:06.801
Mm-hm.

23:09.471 --> 23:11.389
Oh, there's my friend.

23:11.556 --> 23:13.808
It was nice to meet you, Dr. Martin.

23:14.393 --> 23:17.144
LUKA: I will see you at school.
- Yeah.

23:24.027 --> 23:27.530
JEREMY: Hey, sorry I was late. You okay?
- Yeah.

23:28.323 --> 23:31.492
And you're sure Elijah's dead?

23:31.660 --> 23:32.827
Beyond dead.

23:33.328 --> 23:35.704
Trevor was a good man.

23:35.872 --> 23:40.835
Helped me with my dissertation on
sexual deviance in the Baroque period.

23:41.002 --> 23:43.170
I was going for my psych Ph.D.

23:43.338 --> 23:45.506
Slate's been in college since '74.

23:45.674 --> 23:49.885
When I was turned. I have 18 degrees,
three masters and four Ph.D.s.

23:50.053 --> 23:51.178
The point?

23:52.055 --> 23:55.099
Exactly. I mean, what is the point?

23:55.308 --> 23:57.226
What should I be doing
with my eternity?

23:57.394 --> 23:59.812
If you have an answer,
please enlighten me.

24:00.188 --> 24:02.440
We need your help.

24:02.607 --> 24:05.901
If someone wanted to get in touch with
Klaus, how'd you hook him up?

24:06.069 --> 24:07.528
- Craigslist.
- Really?

24:07.696 --> 24:11.407
Seriously, I respond to a personal ad
that gets sent to somebody...

24:11.575 --> 24:14.785
...who knows somebody
who knows Elijah.

24:14.953 --> 24:16.620
Who's dead.

24:16.830 --> 24:19.748
And that's where my connection ends.

25:03.460 --> 25:06.962
- Ha-ha-ha. Man, you are bad.
- Oh, I told you.

25:07.130 --> 25:10.466
- Cheat if you need your dignity back.
- Come on, hit the ball.

25:10.634 --> 25:13.177
All right. Hey, I got winner, guys.
I got winner.

25:13.345 --> 25:15.513
Get ready.
This slaughter's almost over.

25:16.723 --> 25:20.309
- So where's your dad?
- Nice. I'll see him back home.

25:24.231 --> 25:25.773
[SIGHS]

25:25.982 --> 25:28.025
- Okay, now I'm leaving.
- Wait.

25:28.193 --> 25:30.611
No, no, no.
You have two seconds to come clean.

25:30.779 --> 25:33.739
- What do you mean?
- I'd believe the innocent act better...

25:33.907 --> 25:37.952
...if I didn't know how good you were
at providing a distraction on demand.

25:38.537 --> 25:39.620
Where's Elena?

25:43.333 --> 25:44.833
[EXHALES]

25:45.418 --> 25:47.253
I can't tell you.

25:47.420 --> 25:49.463
You can't tell me.
Are you kidding me?

25:49.631 --> 25:53.300
I'm sorry, but I can't tell you.

25:53.468 --> 25:55.928
Elena was kidnapped.
She could've been killed.

25:56.096 --> 25:59.265
- You're not gonna tell me where she is?
- She's not in any danger.

25:59.432 --> 26:01.725
I would not have let her
put herself in danger.

26:01.893 --> 26:03.852
Put herself in danger where?
What are...?

26:06.523 --> 26:10.568
- She's with Damon, isn't she?
- Ew. No.

26:10.735 --> 26:13.028
Then where...? Where is she?

26:13.196 --> 26:14.989
Listen, if you're my friend...

26:15.156 --> 26:17.491
...like you've been pretending
to be all day...

26:17.659 --> 26:19.702
...then you'll tell me where she is.

26:20.161 --> 26:22.037
Stefan...

26:23.081 --> 26:24.248
...I am your friend.

26:24.416 --> 26:26.208
But I'm also Elena's friend.

26:26.376 --> 26:29.044
And I'm sorry...

26:29.212 --> 26:32.089
...but I'm not going to tell you
where she is.

26:36.845 --> 26:38.053
[SCOFFS]

26:43.852 --> 26:45.811
So how much of your little story
is true?

26:45.979 --> 26:48.105
I have no reason to lie, Elena.

26:48.273 --> 26:52.234
I have no reason to do anything
but sit here and read and rot.

26:52.402 --> 26:56.530
Okay, assuming it's even partially true,
that's the reason why you came back.

26:56.698 --> 26:59.742
Because you wanted to be the one
to hand me over to Klaus.

27:00.660 --> 27:05.289
Five hundred years on the run, I figured
maybe he'd be willing to strike a deal.

27:05.457 --> 27:07.541
So you got Mason
to find you the moonstone.

27:07.959 --> 27:09.084
Right again.

27:09.252 --> 27:11.545
What else is needed
to break the curse?

27:11.713 --> 27:13.839
Look who's getting smarter.

27:14.007 --> 27:17.092
It's not just me or the stone, is it?

27:20.388 --> 27:22.181
Otherwise there would be no reason...

27:22.349 --> 27:25.017
...to trigger Tyler Lockwood's
werewolf curse.

27:25.393 --> 27:26.810
Witches and their spells.

27:26.978 --> 27:29.605
So many ingredients,
so many people to sacrifice.

27:30.607 --> 27:32.024
So you need a werewolf.

27:32.484 --> 27:34.610
Believe it or not,
they're hard to come by.

27:34.778 --> 27:37.363
- What else?
- A witch to do the spell.

27:37.530 --> 27:40.157
Mine bailed,
but little Bonnie will do just fine.

27:40.325 --> 27:42.034
- What else?
- A vampire.

27:43.912 --> 27:45.746
Caroline.

27:46.581 --> 27:50.501
Could have been anyone, I suppose,
but I like the poetry of Caroline.

27:52.379 --> 27:55.756
So you were gonna just hand us all over
to be killed.

27:59.344 --> 28:01.512
Better you die than I.

28:12.816 --> 28:15.317
Elijah moved around during the day.

28:15.485 --> 28:18.737
Which means the Original people
knew the secret of the day ring.

28:18.905 --> 28:22.116
Now, why would Klaus wanna lift
the curse of the sun and the moon?

28:22.283 --> 28:24.618
To keep the werewolves
from lifting it.

28:25.412 --> 28:27.663
If a vampire breaks the sun curse...

28:27.831 --> 28:31.375
...the werewolves are stuck with
the curse of the moon and vice-versa.

28:31.543 --> 28:33.252
But werewolves are all but extinct.

28:33.420 --> 28:36.839
Well, true, I've never seen one,
but rumor has it...

28:37.006 --> 28:38.799
Not such a rumor.

28:38.967 --> 28:40.968
Mystic Falls?

28:42.220 --> 28:45.723
God, I've got to visit this place.
It sounds awesome.

28:45.890 --> 28:49.101
DAMON: "Awesome"
doesn't even begin to describe it.

28:49.269 --> 28:52.563
Wait, can we stop the curse
from being broken at all?

28:52.731 --> 28:54.314
SLATER:
What do you mean?

28:54.482 --> 28:58.026
Can we render the moonstone useless
and stop the curse from being broken?

28:58.194 --> 29:02.823
Well, yeah, probably,
but why would you wanna do that?

29:02.991 --> 29:04.992
Tell me how.

29:05.160 --> 29:08.704
SLATER: You think I'm gonna help you
do something that will piss off an Original...

29:08.872 --> 29:10.706
...and keep me from walking in the sun?

29:10.874 --> 29:15.252
DAMON: You wanna walk in the sun?
I can make that happen, if you help us.

29:17.213 --> 29:18.589
[SCREAMING AND YELLING]

29:24.220 --> 29:25.846
Oh, my God.

29:37.442 --> 29:39.067
[SCREAMING AND CRYING]

29:46.117 --> 29:47.284
Let's go.

29:50.705 --> 29:52.206
[ROSE CRYING]

29:56.795 --> 29:58.921
- You're gonna be okay.
- I know. I just...

29:59.088 --> 30:00.506
- Who was behind that?
- I don't know.

30:00.673 --> 30:02.841
- Where's Slater?
- Iowa by now. Who knows?

30:03.009 --> 30:05.511
- He's not behind this. He's a good guy.
- Then who?

30:05.678 --> 30:08.138
It's Klaus. Don't you understand?

30:08.890 --> 30:12.017
You don't know this man. We're dead.
We're all dead.

30:14.020 --> 30:15.521
[SOBBING]

30:30.745 --> 30:31.870
LUKA:
Hey, Bonnie.

30:36.125 --> 30:38.001
I'm sorry about earlier.

30:38.169 --> 30:43.131
My dad. He's not very subtle
with the whole Bennett-Salem question.

30:44.926 --> 30:47.594
He picked up on you,
but he was just fishing around.

30:47.762 --> 30:49.429
He didn't mean any harm.

30:49.597 --> 30:51.640
I felt something too.

30:51.808 --> 30:55.394
I know. That's why we're having
this conversation right now.

30:55.562 --> 30:57.271
He, uh...

30:58.606 --> 31:00.399
He doesn't like for anyone to know...

31:02.527 --> 31:06.488
...but we were both worried
that you would nail us.

31:17.500 --> 31:20.377
He just wants us to fit in here.
For once.

31:20.545 --> 31:23.422
It's tough, Bonnie, being different.

31:23.965 --> 31:25.591
You're a witch?

31:27.218 --> 31:31.555
Well, we prefer the term "warlock."

31:43.568 --> 31:44.776
Elena.

31:45.111 --> 31:48.989
- Stefan, what are you doing here?
- I could ask you the same question.

31:49.365 --> 31:50.574
Caroline told you.

31:50.742 --> 31:52.409
No, she kept your secret.

31:52.577 --> 31:55.412
It didn't take long to figure out
what was so important...

31:55.580 --> 31:58.373
...that you'd keep it from me.
- I knew you'd stop me.

31:58.541 --> 32:01.501
Listen to me.
Whatever she said to you is a lie.

32:01.669 --> 32:03.921
Do not listen to her.
She is a liar, Elena.

32:04.088 --> 32:05.380
What if she isn't?

32:06.507 --> 32:09.259
- You didn't hear what she said.
- You don't have to worry.

32:09.427 --> 32:11.386
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you.

32:11.554 --> 32:14.306
That's the problem. You won't.

32:16.142 --> 32:19.061
But you'll die trying,
how is that any better?

32:20.063 --> 32:22.230
There's nothing you can do, Stefan.

32:22.732 --> 32:25.192
I haven't even told you
the best part of the story.

32:59.477 --> 33:01.061
[GASPS]

33:04.607 --> 33:06.191
[PANTING]

33:08.027 --> 33:10.612
No, no, no. Mama.

33:14.200 --> 33:15.742
[SOBBING]

33:21.624 --> 33:23.250
No.

33:26.254 --> 33:28.338
KATHERINE:
He killed them.

33:28.506 --> 33:30.590
My entire family.

33:30.758 --> 33:32.551
Just to get back at me for running.

33:33.428 --> 33:37.431
Whatever you do to escape Klaus,
he will get his vengeance.

33:37.598 --> 33:41.393
On your friends, your family,
on anyone that you've ever loved.

33:41.561 --> 33:42.644
No, look at me.

33:42.812 --> 33:45.147
No. Do not listen to her, okay?

33:47.442 --> 33:48.692
Always the protector.

33:49.819 --> 33:52.863
But even you must realize
that she's doomed.

33:53.031 --> 33:55.032
There's nothing you can do to stop it.

33:57.702 --> 34:01.121
Unless, of course, you have this.

34:01.289 --> 34:03.957
- What?
- Oh, no. There it is.

34:04.333 --> 34:06.001
That's the ultimate lie, isn't it?

34:06.169 --> 34:09.963
You spun this whole thing so that
we would have to get the stone from you.

34:11.591 --> 34:13.842
I didn't spin anything, Stefan.
It's the truth.

34:14.010 --> 34:15.677
No. Let me guess.

34:15.844 --> 34:19.181
You wanna trade that stone
for your freedom, hmm?

34:19.348 --> 34:22.350
You manipulative, psychotic bitch.

34:22.851 --> 34:24.811
My freedom?

34:24.978 --> 34:28.356
That's where you're wrong, Stefan.
I don't want my freedom.

34:28.524 --> 34:31.818
Because when Klaus shows up
to kill us all and he will...

34:32.695 --> 34:33.904
...I'll be in the tomb.

34:34.072 --> 34:36.697
Where no vampire will enter
because they can't get out.

34:38.951 --> 34:41.536
I'll be the safest psychotic bitch
in town.

35:21.661 --> 35:23.120
I'm sorry about today.

35:23.287 --> 35:25.705
I didn't know that was gonna happen.

35:27.375 --> 35:28.959
I believe you.

35:29.544 --> 35:31.545
And I wish we could save Elena.

35:31.712 --> 35:33.046
I know that you want to.

35:33.881 --> 35:35.423
And I will.

35:38.553 --> 35:40.220
You remind me of Trevor.

35:41.055 --> 35:43.473
Why? Why him?

35:43.683 --> 35:46.226
Because he always talked a big game.

35:46.394 --> 35:48.895
He was always working an angle.

35:49.230 --> 35:51.940
But he was the best friend
anyone could ever hope for.

35:52.108 --> 35:54.067
Where'd that get him?

35:56.737 --> 35:58.071
Dead.

36:01.075 --> 36:03.243
And my loyalty to him
almost got me dead too.

36:05.121 --> 36:06.997
To friendship.

36:11.085 --> 36:12.460
You're right to fight it.

36:16.007 --> 36:18.133
The way you feel about her.

36:19.302 --> 36:21.136
And why's that?

36:22.597 --> 36:24.931
Because if we wanna survive...

36:25.099 --> 36:27.934
...we need to not care about anyone.

36:31.439 --> 36:33.523
Caring gets you dead, huh?

36:36.027 --> 36:39.779
It might just be time to turn
the switch off on your emotions.

36:46.287 --> 36:47.954
I will if you will.

37:29.997 --> 37:31.915
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

37:47.181 --> 37:48.348
STEFAN:
Elena.

37:48.516 --> 37:51.685
- I can't talk about it, Stefan.
- You have to. Don't shut me out.

37:54.188 --> 37:55.313
Elena, please.

37:56.816 --> 38:00.026
I wanted to know the truth, Stefan,
and I got it.

38:01.946 --> 38:04.364
It's not just me that's in danger.

38:04.532 --> 38:08.702
It's... It's Caroline and it's Tyler
and it's Bonnie.

38:08.869 --> 38:10.745
They're all part of breaking the curse.

38:12.540 --> 38:14.874
I can't blame anyone else anymore.

38:15.042 --> 38:19.629
It's not because you came into town
or because you and I fell in love.

38:19.839 --> 38:22.966
That's not why everyone I love
is in danger. It's because of me.

38:23.134 --> 38:26.052
Everything is because of me and I...

38:26.220 --> 38:27.637
[SOBBING]

39:36.499 --> 39:38.792
It's a lie, you know.

39:38.959 --> 39:40.794
There's no switch you can turn off.

39:42.004 --> 39:45.465
Sure, when you're a newbie,
but after a couple hundred years...

39:47.134 --> 39:48.802
...you just have to pretend.

39:51.055 --> 39:52.764
[PHONE RINGING]

39:58.646 --> 40:00.063
- Hello?
- Rose?

40:00.231 --> 40:02.649
Slater? Are you okay?

40:02.817 --> 40:06.152
Yes, I took off, I'm sorry.
I was frigging freaked.

40:06.320 --> 40:07.987
No, I'm sorry to involve you.

40:08.155 --> 40:11.825
Look, I want no part in any of this,
but I did some digging.

40:13.494 --> 40:14.661
Okay. What did you find?

40:14.829 --> 40:18.665
You can destroy the curse,
but you need the moonstone.

40:18.833 --> 40:20.917
How? What do you mean?
I don't follow.

40:21.085 --> 40:24.003
Well, can your friend get the
moonstone? You need it.

40:26.507 --> 40:29.050
Yes, he can get it. What next?

40:29.510 --> 40:30.593
We need a witch.

40:30.761 --> 40:35.014
Get the moonstone. A witch should
be able to figure out the rest.

40:35.349 --> 40:37.267
Good luck, Rose.

40:42.273 --> 40:44.357
ELIJAH:
Very nicely done.

40:44.525 --> 40:47.735
Thanks. I have a degree in theater.

40:51.031 --> 40:54.242
How can you compel me? A vampire
can't compel another vampire.

40:54.410 --> 40:56.870
I'm a special vampire.

40:57.246 --> 40:58.830
What, because you're an Original?

40:59.206 --> 41:00.457
Hmm.

41:03.419 --> 41:05.044
Now...

41:05.212 --> 41:08.381
...I want you to take this
and drive it through your heart.

41:10.634 --> 41:12.886
But that would kill me forever.

41:13.429 --> 41:15.054
ELIJAH:
I know.

41:17.725 --> 41:19.767
But it's necessary.

41:36.911 --> 41:38.828
Was it really?

41:39.288 --> 41:41.623
It had to be done.

41:44.126 --> 41:45.668
He delivered his message.

41:49.298 --> 41:51.257
Won't be long now.

